Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "tobi" in different forms and positions, along with their English translations in parentheses:

1. *Tobi* se ne sviđa ova hrana. (You don't like this food.)
2. Rekao sam *tobi* da dođeš u 5 sati. (I told you to come at 5 o'clock.)
3. *Tobi* bih dao ovaj komad torte. (I would give this piece of cake to you.)
4. *Tobi* će biti potrebna veća torba za putovanje. (You will need a bigger bag for the trip.)
5. *Tobi* je dobrodošao na slavlje. (You are welcome to the party.)
6. Nadam se da ćeš *tobi* biti ugodno u našoj kući. (I hope you will feel comfortable in our home.)
7. *Tobi* želim srećan rođendan! (Happy birthday to you!)
8. *Tobi* se divim načinu na koji rješavaš probleme. (I admire the way you solve problems.)

Note that "tobi" is a pronoun in Serbian that is equivalent to the English word "you." It can be used as the subject, object, or indirect object of a sentence, and can be declined to indicate case (e.g. "tobi" for the dative case, "tebe" for the accusative case, etc.).